==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epicranium
<hw>Ep`i*cra"ni*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Epi-</er>, and <er>Cranium</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The upper and superficial part of the head,
including the scalp, muscles, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>The dorsal wall of the head
of insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epictetian</ent>⟦br⟧
